File: Eskom will implement rolling blackouts. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has ramped up power cuts to Stage 6 starting from 2pm on Thursday until midnight. Stage 6 will continue from 5am until midnight on Friday. Eskom says a minimum of Stage 4 will be required continuously over the weekend. The power utility says the increased power cuts is being caused by striking workers as routine maintenance isn't being done.  Eskom implements stage 6 blackouts from 2pm until midnight. Stage 4 will continue from midnight until 5am on Friday. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/Yw3d5od26F